b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48450.htm)  [Next](sbe48452.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n4\\. On account of direct scriptural statement.\n\nScripture itself directly declares knowledge to be subordinate to works,\n'whatever he does with knowledge, with faith, with the Upanishad, that is more\nvigorous'. Nor can it be said that this text refers, on the ground of leading\nsubject-matter (prakara _n_ a), to the Udgitha only; for direct scriptural\nstatement ( _s_ uti) is stronger than subject-matter,\n\np. 689\n\nand the words 'whatever he does with knowledge' clearly refer to knowledge in\ngeneral.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 5. On account of the taking hold together](sbe48452.htm)\n\n"